reviewText: The West Bank Story is a very funny and  enjoyable movie depicting the sad circumstances in Israel.  It is like the West Side Story movie of the 60's

It's different. I got this copy as a gift, but saw it a few years ago. Comedy version of West Side Story/Romeo and Juliet taking place in Israel/Occupied territories. Very funny and cute, as the kids of rival felafel and hummus stands-a Jew and a Palestinian-fall in love. Not an "art" movie, but worth watching.
